snippet.textDisplay:
However short it might've been, this was my favorite Superman/Clark thus far in the Arrowverse. Sorry if this offends anybody, but I've felt like Supergirl's Superman has been used too often to try to prop up Kara. To me, he feels like more of a support tool. THIS Clark Kent stands on his own; confident, cool, but pure. Doesn't have any powers yet still feels more badass than the Arrowverse Superman.


Also, his dynamic with Jon Cryer was great at demonstrating the contrast between Lex and Superman. Lex, a man of massive wealth and intellect, cannot put aside his petty jealousy and hatred against any Superman, even in the middle of this massive crisis. While Clark gave up his godlike powers in exchange for a simple family life at a farm.
